         <abstract>
            <p>The increasing trend of the business community to "farm out" various peripheral functions, for example, cleaning, maintenance, security, protection, engineering, food dispensing, etc., adds to the growing investment stature of the burgeoning service industry. This article presents an in-depth analysis of why the equities of service companies merit the attention of all segments of the investment community. The author pinpoints the characteristics of the industry, its unique features, and reasons for offering attractive money-making investment opportunities. The article suggests that investing in business service companies allows one to participate in some of the major favorable trends in our economy yet avoid some of the problems confronting many leading companies today.</p>
          </abstract>
